F:\ykgcuts\ykgcuts.doc Notes on producing all years flightline lat/long endpoint coordinates within the sampling intensity stratification on Yukon Delta Coastal Zone Requested by Bill Eldridge 10-1-02 updated: 7-24-03
information will be given to Jack Hodges to be used in developing a population analysis program
Process: use existing flightline coverages, editted designs for 1985-1997, designed 1998-2002, and overlay with polygon stratification coverage BIGSID (sampling intensity dissolved) with ARC identity command to split lines at stratum boundaries. Project line coverages from utm zone 3 to geographic, then ungenerate each to a text file with split-arc id, lat and long of each end. *.txt files will contain the new arc ids along with the original transect number that they came from.
Ran f:\amls\idoutmul.aml with readfile.txt
project all split flightline coverages to geographic, then ungenerate
